snippet: Washington and its allies have said they think North Korea’s rocket program has less to do with putting a satellite into orbit than with developing a vehicle for a nuclear warhead.
abstract: North Korea launches long-range rocket that appears to reach as far as the Philippines, an apparent success for leader Kim Jong-un; country says its ostensible goal is to put observation satellite into orbit, but United States and its allies have said they think North Korea’s rocket program is part of an effort to develop a vehicle for a nuclear warhead.

byline.original: By CHOE SANG-HUN and DAVID E. SANGER
byline.contributor: Choe Sang-hun reported from Seoul, and David E. Sanger from Washington.

lead_paragraph: Washington and its allies have said they think North Korea’s rocket program has less to do with putting a satellite into orbit than with developing a vehicle for a nuclear warhead.

headline.seo: North Korea Launches Rocket, Defying Likely Sanctions
headline.main: North Koreans Launch Rocket in Defiant Act
headline.print_headline: North Koreans Launch Rocket In Defiant Act
